The new Secretary of Homeland Security has replaced the word &ldquo;terrorism&rdquo; with &ldquo;man-caused disasters.&rdquo;
 I did not use the word &ldquo;terrorism,&rdquo; I referred to &ldquo;man-caused&rdquo; disasters. That is perhaps only a nuance, but it demonstrates that we want to move away from the politics of fear toward a policy of being prepared for all risks that can occur.
 I assume that appointing an idiot like Napolitano to the cabinet qualifies as a man-cause disaster.
